From: Paulo Zanoni <paulo.r.zanoni@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 1 Apr 2014 15:37:13 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 0141/1369] drm/i915: don't forget to uninstall the PM IRQs

commit c71ae0148e103fbad49c49d4c2ba27d46bb8eef5 upstream.

It's the only thing missing, apparently.

v2: - Fix typo (Ben).

Reviewed-by: Ben Widawsky <ben@bwidawsk.net>
Signed-off-by: Paulo Zanoni <paulo.r.zanoni@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_irq.c |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_irq.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_irq.c
index 847a9c8..ba8c1a5 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_irq.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_irq.c
@@ -3374,6 +3374,8 @@ static void ironlake_irq_uninstall(struct drm_device *dev)
 		I915_WRITE(GEN7_ERR_INT, I915_READ(GEN7_ERR_INT));
 
 	GEN5_IRQ_FINI(GT);
+	if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 6)
+		GEN5_IRQ_FINI(GEN6_PM);
 
 	if (HAS_PCH_NOP(dev))
 		return;
